window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The only thing I ever loved more than hockey? Skylar Ward.</b></p> <p>The one who got away, or rather the one I pushed away and into the arms of my hockey nemesis when I left for a D1 college hockey team.</p> <p>He broke her heart, too. The only difference—he didn't love her.</p> <p>I did. I still do.</p> <p>I think she loves me too. Even if she won't admit it. Even if she doesn't want to.</p> <p>The sexy single mom is running the best defense I've ever encountered. And as a top forward in the NHL, that's saying something.</p> <p>Lucky for me, her son loves hockey. He's my biggest fan, and I'm his.</p> <p>Getting Skylar to give me a second chance isn't going to be easy. Good thing I play to win.</p> <p>But what if our past isn't the only thing standing in the way?</p> <p>Second Chance Player <i>kicks off a brand new series from bestselling author R.C. Stephens. Get ready for an adorable five-year-old boy, a hockey player with a broken heart, and a strong heroine who has learned to beat the odds. There is no cheating and a guaranteed HEA because they are soul mates.</i></p> <p><i>Intended for mature listeners.</i></p>"; 
